   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>THE TRAINING AND THE PRACTICE OF THE VITAL GROUPS MESSAGE THIRTEEN HAVING ENTERED THROUGH THE NARROW GATE AND WALKING ON THE CONSTRICTED WAY Scripture Reading: Matt 7:13-14 OUTLINE In the decree of the kingdom's constitution, Christ displayed the two possible ways of people's life and work before God Matt 7:13-14: The broad way: Through the wide gate.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>Leading to destruction.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>Many walking on this broad way who have entered through the wide gate.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>According to the worldly systems satisfying the natural tastes.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>To get the crowd.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>To maintain a career of man.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Achieving man's enterprise.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>The constricted way: Through the narrow gate.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Leading to life.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>Few walking on this constricted way who have found it.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>According to the divine regulations fulfilling the spiritual requests.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>To bring in God's elect.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>To bear the testimony of Jesus Christ.</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>Carrying out God's economy.</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>For the building up of the church of God the Body of Christ: The entry in all things must be narrow: In preaching the gospel.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>In teaching the truth.</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>In edifying the believers.</S>
   <S PAR='18' RSNT='1' SNO='18'>In maturing the saints.</S>
   <S PAR='19' RSNT='1' SNO='19'>The ongoing in all the works must be constricted: In saving the sinners.</S>
   <S PAR='20' RSNT='1' SNO='20'>In feeding the new believers.</S>
   <S PAR='21' RSNT='1' SNO='21'>In perfecting the saints.</S>
   <S PAR='22' RSNT='1' SNO='22'>In building up the church of God the Body of Christ.</S>
   </TEXT>
